  "name": "bigquery_server_maria_pipeorder",
  "notes": "Headline feature is ORDER BY (SORT) appearing before SELECT, inspired by BigQuery's pipe syntax concept and kdb-style sort-first thinking. MariaDB contributes hash-comments, IFNULL alias, and MOD keyword. SQL Server contributes OUTER-explicit join keywords, integer-division promote, and div-by-zero-as-null. The SUBTRACT keyword for EXCEPT, required semicolons, and rows_unbounded_to_current window frame default add further distinctiveness. Count-distinct includes nulls (BigQuery-like). Case-preserving identifiers with 0-based arrays round out the profile.",
